  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Beef a la Brigitte</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Cyberealm</cat>
        <cat>Meats</cat>
        <cat>Microwave</cat></categories>
      <yield>5</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1 1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Cooked, cubed roast beef</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Stick of margarine</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Flour</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1 1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Hot water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Mustard</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Salt and pepper to taste</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  In a microwave bowl, melt margarine; add flour, hot water and milk,
  and stir, microwaving on HIGH for 1 minute at a time after each
  addition. Stir well after each minute until the gravy is nice and
  smooth. Add the mustard and salt and pepper to taste. Heat through
  well, about 3 minutes on HIGH. Add beef and microwave until warm.
  Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles or rice and a vegetable.
  
  Source: Brigitte Sealing, Cyberealm BBS Watertown NY 315-786-1120
  
  File ftp://ftp.idiscover.co.uk/pub/food/mealmaster/recipes/mmcyber4.zip
 
</step></directions></recipe></recipeml>
